{"questionId":"5764","questionHtml":"<p>A student measures the radius <em>r </em>of a sphere with an absolute uncertainty Δ<em>r</em>. What is the fractional uncertainty in the volume of the sphere?</p>\n<p>A. &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\left( {\\frac{{\\Delta r}}{r}} \\right)^3}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi>\n              <mi>r</mi>\n            </mrow>\n            <mi>r</mi>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>B. &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"3\\frac{{\\Delta r}}{r}\">\n  <mn>3</mn>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi>\n      <mi>r</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mi>r</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>C. &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"4\\pi \\frac{{\\Delta r}}{r}\">\n  <mn>4</mn>\n  <mi>π</mi>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi>\n      <mi>r</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mi>r</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>D. &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"4\\pi {\\left( {\\frac{{\\Delta r}}{r}} \\right)^3}\">\n  <mn>4</mn>\n  <mi>π</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi>\n              <mi>r</mi>\n            </mrow>\n            <mi>r</mi>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>B</p>","meta":{"questionId":"5764","referenceCode":"18M.1.SL.TZ1.1","subjectId":"46-dp